Vice President Joe Biden and his wife, Jill, expressed their shock and sorrow over the shooting in Aurora, Colorado. They emphasized that the tragedy resonates with all Americans because it could have been anyone's child in any town. They understand the pain and helplessness that parents feel in such situations. The Bidens extended their heartfelt sympathies to all those affected and stated that the nation's prayers are with the victims and their families. They also expressed solidarity with the city of Aurora and the state of Colorado during this time of mourning.